    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:sec>\n                  <jats:title>Aim</jats:title>\n                  <jats:p>To develop a rapid and easy diagnostic assay for detection of SARS-CoV-2 RNA presented in saliva samples.</jats:p>\n                </jats:sec>\n                <jats:sec>\n                  <jats:title>Method</jats:title>\n                  <jats:p>The color-based RT-LAMP was used to detect nucleocapsid (N) gene of SARS-CoV-2 without RNA extraction from saliva.</jats:p>\n                </jats:sec>\n                <jats:sec>\n                  <jats:title>Results</jats:title>\n                  <jats:p>\n                    RNA spiked saliva can be used directly for cDNA synthesis after heat inactivation of the saliva and diluted 2-fold with either water or PBS. For both PCR and LAMP, 20% of saliva did not have obvious effect on the reaction. Saliva did not interfere with RT-LAMP when the volume of saliva was less than 20% of the total volume. The sensitivity of the RT-LAMP reached to 1.034\u00d710\n                    <jats:sup>-5</jats:sup>\n                    ng/\u00b5l (475 copies/\u03bcl). The RT-LAMP assay was validated by testing 20 RNA spiked saliva samples. The assay specificity was similar to that of data without saliva.\n                  </jats:p>\n                </jats:sec>\n                <jats:sec>\n                  <jats:title>Conclusions</jats:title>\n                  <jats:p>The RT-LAMP colorimetric assay can be used as a screening method with the advantages of being rapid, easy to use than the qRT-PCR.</jats:p>\n                </jats:sec>",
